I constantly stop by getting some food in here. I enjoy the quick service and well made food. I recommend this place.
Overpriced, small portions, bland and lacked flavor, greasy.

Overpriced  I've had amazing dim sum and I've had horrifying dim sum. The one thing I can say is at least this place has neither of the two.  But I think the flat dumplings need to be finished in a pan.  Average budget per person: $35 w/delivery and tip
Word restaurant for take out. It takes more then an hour to pick.

Great people that make traditional foods filled with the spirit of love
We had a really poor meal from here.  The dumplings were good, but the two main dishes we had were significantly below average.
Best wonton soup in town 😄
Splendid flavor, texture, all the culinary right stuff that I don't have the exact vocabulary for!
This place is really good. Straightforward Chinese food with a specialty of dumplings and potstickers. Really good flavors. Great Oakland crowd.
They make a mean dumpling
The dumings are OK but something is missing to take them into deliciousness for the price. Tried the Ying Yang, Dragon and Siu Mai.
The glass noodles are great. The owner is friendly!
Great food, great service, but the menu was complicated, and we never did understand all the options...
Nice tasty classics done well

Overall this restaurant is pretty good. Bit of a hit or miss situation with each dish, unfortunately. The hot and sour soup was some of the best I've ever had, and the dragon dumplings were excellent. The lamb, however, was overcooked and rubbery. I would not recommend any lamb dishes here.
Wonton soup was good and the dessert option banana fritters is really good!!

Not your average Chinese takeout. We were looking for easy comfort food and were pleasantly surprised by delicious the food was. This just became our go to Chinese takeout choice in the Grand Lake area.
The service and food was prompt and well done!
Love their dumplings
Highly recommend the Firecracker wontons, Szcehuan noodles, and the Sesame chicken. Possibly the best Chinese I've had in the Bay area, if not ever.
Great food, good service and reasonable prices.

Not the best, not the worst. The chicken was a little dry and we probably wont go here again but it was satisfactory for what we wanted at the time.
The mushuuuu style!?!?!?!?!?!?

A bit pricier than a regular Chinese dumpling restaurant, but the ambiance is nice, perfect for a date night.  We ordered 2 dumpling dishes (Chive/Pork, and Firecracker) and a garlic noodles dish.  All of them were quite tasty.
Fresh and delicious and priced very well.
Best food and service!
Greasy. Dumplings tasted like thawed from frozen.
OMG this is the best. Our new fav restaurant!!
Good garlic noodles.

Solid neighborhood "go-to." The Ying-Yang dumplings were yummy (why seven pieces?) but the main course "Dragon and Phoenix" was just good. Not great, not bad, a solid "good." Great people, though and a good vibe.
Cooking and flavors catered toward Western taste buds. Fine if that's what you're looking for.  Service is friendly and environment is clean.
Good but not great

So delicious. We only got appetizers but can't wait till our next visit to Oakland to try more off the menu.
Good food and price
Not bad Asian food
Delicious noodles and dumplings. Grateful to have Qi in the neighborhood.

I would say 3.5 stars.  We had a baby two months back and so cooking at home in the beginning was tough so our friends gave us grubhub as a gift to order food from outside - genius idea!  We were feeling like asian cuisine so gave Qi …
A+ Love the food!
Good service and Better dumplings. 6 of us, 6 different dumplings, wor wonton soup, 2 noodle dishes and eggplant with crispy tofu. All well done and very tasty. Everyone loved it.
Wow - let’s just say I can’t wait to go back here! Absolutely delicious!
Chicken and chive shui Mai were excellent. The Dan Dan Noodles were unique but unfortunately the best way. Definitely going back.

Our regular favorite dumpling spot; consistently yummy, friendly owner and staff, and a good menu. Low key atmosphere great for a casual date. Favorites: Green dumpling, Dragon dumplings, Cilantro Chicken dumplings, garlic noodles, friend oysters (with wonderful green dipping sauce!), and fried seaweed mushrooms.
Friendly,  reasonable prices, quick service, & very tasty food
No MSG , fresh and delicious!!
Really yummy stuff. Never disappointed. Try the black pepper udon noodles and the chicken wings.

Outstanding example this cuisine in a friendly, helpful low key atmosphere. A whole range of flavors and spice intensities as well as dishes and preparation that meet the gamut of dietary needs and desires. Relatively modest prices for an upscale location.

This place has really good food, flavors are well developed in every dish I've had. I'm vegetarian and they have a lot of yummy options this is a plus plus. Probably my favorite restaurant on the block.
Overpriced, bougie dumplings, overly fried with not very good sauce and minimal vegies
The food is good but a bit oily. There are nice vegetarian options. The portions are good.
Very fresh flavors, clearly no msg. The beef lettuce cups, wings and dragon dumplings were amazing.
I really like their chicken wings.
Garlic spinach is SOOOO delicious. Also really liked the honey chicken wings :)

I was really dissapointed in the lack of flavors considering the description and the price. Everything sounded so good but it was all pretty flat. For example, the dumpling with jalapeños were bland and jalapeño. Servers were all a little grumpy, too.
Really great house made dumplings. I loved the Ying Yang dumplings. We will come back for the Dragon dumplings. Wonderful!
It was ok, was expecting more dumplings​ because the name, but there weren't that much.
Dumplings were tasty but cold

Cute little restaurant with good service. The dumplings taste so fresh and the pork buns are to die for. There are so many great tapas selections so i will definitely be back to try more. It's nicely located by shops and bars.

Boy were we lucky to find Qi Dumpling Lounge! After having seriously the best bowl of wonton soup I've ever had, I just knew Qi had to be on our Grand Lake Cultural Cuisine food tour! Plus, the owner Shirleen and her staff are great to work with and provide awesome service.
New place that has great, fresh, flavorful food. Dumplings were fantastic and garlic noodles were great as well. Great ambiance as well.
Great dumplings! Especially the dragon dumplings. Yum!
Very nice, they offered me a takeout menu right away. 12/10 would read menu again.
